Be careful returning astd::string_viewstd::string_viewcan be used as the return value of a function. However, this is often dangerous.Because local variables are destroyed at the end of the function, returning astd::string_viewthat is viewing a local variable will result in the returnedstd::string_viewbeing invalid, and further use of thatstd::string_viewwill result in undefined behavior. For example:#include <iostream>
